            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "There is a long history in the medical field of doctors experimenting on and abusing prisoners, including in Massachusetts. While current rules prohibit the state Department of Corrections from ‚Äúthe use of an inmate(s) for medical, pharmaceutical, or cosmetic experiments,‚Äù in 1942, a professor at Harvard Medical School ",
