            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://abcnews.go.com/US/LegalCenter/story?id=2940289&page=1",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " on a similar proposal in South Carolina, ‚ÄúIt's probably going to be considered a violation of federal law. Congress passed the National Organ Transplant Act in 1984 that makes it a federal crime \"to knowingly acquire, receive, or otherwise transfer any human organ for valuable consideration for use in human transplantation. It is likely 180 days off a sentence could constitute ‚Äòvaluable consideration.‚Äô‚Äù",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
