            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", ‚ÄúI‚Äôve put more effort into this bill after visiting a friend, who I consider a brother, in the hospital who is required to have dialysis 3 to 4 times a week while he awaits a kidney transplant. He‚Äôs a father of three children, and he is in stage 4 of kidney failure‚Ä¶ I love my friend and I‚Äôm praying through this legislation we can extend the chances of life.‚Äù Gonzalez also noted to WHYN that there are significant racial disparities in who needs transplants, bolstering his case for the legislation.",
